.SH NAME
uart_try_toggle_sysrq \- Enables SysRq from serial line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" uart_try_toggle_sysrq
.BI "(struct uart_port *port "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ch "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
uart_port structure where char(s) after BREAK met
.IP "ch" 12
new character in the sequence after received BREAK

Enables magic SysRq when the required sequence is met on port
(see CONFIG_MAGIC_SYSRQ_SERIAL_SEQUENCE).

Returns false if \fIch\fP is out of enabling sequence and should be
handled some other way, true if \fIch\fP was consumed.
